result.execSummary:
The defendant Nena Rea Marshall was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: 2nd/Sub. Drug Off.-Class E/F/G/H/I Fel.], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

9:05 AM Prosecuting attorney Jonathan Ross in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Nena Rea Marshall in court, in custody from the Columbia County Jail.  Attorney Brian William Severson in court for Nena Rea Marshall. Court called 21 CF 696 & 22 CF 93. Waived readings. Rights/Elements. 21 CF 696 Court reviewed right to preliminary hearing, defendant waived. Court found probable cause, bound over. Defendant pled no contest to count 1. Court found defendant guilty on count 1. Counts 2 & 3 dismissed but read in. Court withheld sentence, placed defendant on probation for 4 years, successful completion of the Columbia County Drug Treatment Court, 30 days jail imposed/stayed to be used at the discretion of the Columbia County Drug Treatment Court team, pay costs of $518.00, pay $31.85 in restitution, submit DNA sample. 4 days credit. 22 CF 93 Defendant pled no contest to counts 1 & 3. Court found defendant guilty on counts 1 & 3. Counts 2 & 4 dismissed but read in. Court withheld sentence, placed defendant on probation for 4 years, successful completion of the Columbia County Drug Treatment Court, 30 days jail imposed/stayed to be used at the discretion of the Columbia County Drug Treatment Court team, pay costs of $518.00 in count 1 & $268.00 in count 3, submit DNA sample.
